c relationship with food, Jennifer Manlowe here illuminates the connections between female body, weight, and appetite preoccupations.Manlowe offers social and psychological insights into the most common forms of female suffering-incest and body hatred. The volume is intended as a resource for professionals, advocates, friends of survivors, and most importantly, the survivor of incest herself as she attempts to understand the links of meaning in her mind between her incest experience and her subsequent eating disorder.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aAdult child sexual abuse victimsxReligious lifezUnited States. 0aAdult child sexual abuse victims. 0aBody image. 0aChristianityvControversial literaturexControversial literature. 0aChristianity. 0aEating disorderszUnited StatesxEtiology. 0aEating disorders. 0aIncestxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aIncest. 0aSexismxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aSexism. 0aTwelve-step programsxReligious aspects. 0aTwelve-step programs. 0aWomenxMental healthzUnited States. 0aWomen. 7aRELIGION / Psychology of Religion.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814763148423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814763148.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK